      "span_text": "Another avenue of research involves replacing the beam splitters of the MZI with nonlinear media (eg.: Lithium Niobate, Rubidium gas, β-Barrium Borate, etc.) These so-called \"non-linear interferometers\" (see Ref. and references therein) can push the sensitivity limit down to ∆φ 2 min = 1/ N nl ( N nl + 2), where N nl is the average number of photons produced by the nonlinearties."
